        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "feat: add Skill Workshop proposals and skill research",
        "body": "## Summary\n\nThis PR adds the governed Skill Workshop path for creating and improving OpenClaw skills.\n\nAgents can now use `skill_research` to draft new skills, propose updates to existing skills, revise pending proposals, inspect/list proposals, and move explicit proposals through apply/reject/quarantine actions. The write path is proposal-first: generated skill work is stored as a pending `PROPOSAL.md` draft and only becomes an active `SKILL.md` after the proposal is applied.\n\n## What changed\n\n- Added durable Skill Workshop proposal storage under OpenClaw state, with `proposal.json`, `PROPOSAL.md`, support files, rollback metadata, and a rebuildable `proposals.json` manifest.\n- Added the `skill_research` agent tool for create, update, revise, list, inspect, apply, reject, and quarantine actions.\n- Added CLI commands under `openclaw skills workshop`.\n- Added Gateway proposal methods for list, inspect, create, update, apply, reject, and quarantine flows.\n- Added proposal support files under standard skill folders, with text-file validation, scanner checks, hash verification, stale-target detection, and guarded apply writes.\n- Added proposal revision support with versioned and dated proposal frontmatter.\n- Added system prompt/tool catalog guidance so agents know when to use `skill_research`.\n- Added docs and changelog entries for the proposal lifecycle.\n\n## Safety\n\n- Generated skills are pending proposals by default.\n- Active skills are not overwritten silently.\n- Apply is workspace-scoped and checks stale target state before writing.\n- Update proposals preserve target baselines and mark stale when live skill/support files change.\n- Support files are validated, scanned, hash-checked, and rejected when unsafe or non-text.\n- Apply writes rollback metadata and uses guarded writes to avoid partial or clobbering publishes.\n- Reject/quarantine only operate on pending proposals.\n\n## Verification\n\n- `git diff --check`\n- Testbox-through-Crabbox `tbx_01kswe55f5t36qthwxwap5rr99`:\n  `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs src/skills/workshop/service.test.ts src/cli/skills-cli.workshop.test.ts src/agents/tools/skill-research-tool.test.ts packages/gateway-protocol/src/schema/agents-models-skills.test.ts src/gateway/server-methods/skills.proposals.test.ts src/agents/system-prompt.test.ts src/agents/tool-catalog.test.ts`\n",
